Company Policy Manual

1. Work‑From‑Home (WFH) Policy
All employees are eligible for a hybrid work‑from‑home schedule.
Employees must be physically present in the office on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays.
Mondays and Fridays are optional remote days.
Employees must ensure availability during core hours: 9 AM to 4 PM EST.

2. Paid Time Off (PTO) Policy
Full‑time employees receive 20 days of Paid Time Off (PTO) per year.
PTO accrues monthly and unused PTO rolls over up to a maximum of 5 days.
Employees must submit PTO requests at least 7 days in advance unless it is an emergency.

3. Technology Stack
The official backend programming language is Python.
The official frontend framework is React.
For mobile development, the company uses React Native.
All production services must follow internal security and compliance guidelines.

4. Security & Compliance
Employees must complete annual security training.
All code must pass automated security scans before deployment.
Sensitive data must be encrypted at rest and in transit.

End of Document.